EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass H.J. Res 64, an amendment to the Constitution of the United States, which would allow Congress and individual states to regulate campaign finance and political spending, and to pass legislation restoring aggregate contribution limits and third party spending limits.
EventItemMatterName: Allow Congress and individual states to regulate campaign finance and political spending, and to pass legislation restoring aggregate contribution limits and third party spending limits. (H.J. Res 64)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Rules, Privileges and Elections
EventItemTitle: Resolution to amend the Rules of the Council in relation to the availability of local laws for review by Council Members
EventItemMatterName: Amend the Rules of the Council in relation to the availability of local laws for review by Council Members.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services to amend its Model Plan for Administrative Naturalization Ceremonies to allow guest speakers to make remarks on the importance of becoming an organ donor.
EventItemMatterName: Citizenship and Immigration Services to amend its Model Plan for Administrative Naturalization Ceremonies to allow guest speakers to make remarks on the importance of becoming an organ donor.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, A.1508/S.1891, to create a property tax abatement for homeowners and a water and sewer charge abatement for not-for-profit entities that install a sewer line check valve
EventItemMatterName: Create a property tax abatement for homeowners and a water and sewer charge abatement for not-for-profit entities that install a sewer line check valve. (A.1508/S.1891)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State legislature to pass and the Governor to enact A.2658 regarding the repeal of reimbursement tax credits to low-wage employers who pay minimum wages to students ages 16 to 19.
EventItemMatterName: Repeal of reimbursement tax credits to low-wage employers who pay minimum wages to students ages 16 to 19. (A.2658)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education not to punish students or parents for opting out of State exams; not to punish schools, principals or teachers if parents opt out of State exams; not to punish superintendents, principals or teachers for informing parents of the right to opt out of State exams; and to provide alternate activities for students who opt out of State exams.
EventItemMatterName: DOE not to punish students or parents for opting out of State exams; not to punish schools, principals or teachers if parents opt out of State exams; not to punish superintendents, principals or teachers for informing parents of the right to opt out of St

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution reaffirming the people’s right to peaceful protest.
EventItemMatterName: Reaffirming the people’s right to peaceful protest.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil and Human Rights
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on President Donald Trump to overturn the directive prohibiting transgender individuals from serving in the military and for U.S. Secretary of Defense James Mattis to continue to allow transgender individuals to serve openly
EventItemMatterName: Overturn the directive prohibiting transgender individuals from serving in the military.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would return control of the subway and bus system to the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Return control of the subway and bus system to NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R. 3246, the Teachers and Parents at the Table Act, which would create an advisory committee of teachers and an advisory committee of parents to advise the Congress and Secretary of Education.
EventItemMatterName: Teachers and Parents at the Table Act (H.R. 3246)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to establish Diwali as an official holiday for New York City public school students.
EventItemMatterName: Establish Diwali as an official holiday for  NYC public school students.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.7063/ S.5563, legislation regarding the creation of a pilot program to improve social and emotional learning in schools.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a pilot program to improve social and emotional learning in schools. (A.7063/ S.5563)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City University of New York (CUNY) to incorporate Diwali as an observed university holiday throughout the CUNY system.
EventItemMatterName: CUNY to incorporate Diwali as an observed university holiday throughout the CUNY system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon United States Food and Drug Administration to remove any blood donation restrictions based on sexual orientation.
EventItemMatterName: FDA to remove any blood donation restrictions based on sexual orientation.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Mental Health, Disabilities and Addiction
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation which designates as professional misconduct, engaging in sexual orientation change efforts by mental health care professionals upon patients under 18 years of age.
EventItemMatterName: Designates as professional misconduct, engaging in sexual orientation change efforts by mental health care professionals upon patients under 18 years of age.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the 115th Congress to pass, and the President to sign, H.R. 2508, which would provide immigration judges with discretionary authority to determine that an immigrant parent of a United States citizen child should not be ordered removed, deported, or excluded from the United States
EventItemMatterName: Provide immigration judges with discretionary authority to determine that an immigrant parent of a US citizen child should not be ordered removed, deported, or excluded from the United States. (H.R. 2508)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Department of Homeland Security to end the practice of placing immigrant detainees in solitary confinement, except in emergency situations.
EventItemMatterName: Dept of Homeland Security to end the practice of placing immigrant detainees in solitary confinement, except in emergency situations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R. 2151/S.954, the Tyler Clementi Higher Education Anti-Harassment Act, which would recognize cyberbullying as a form of harassment and require higher education institutions to enact anti-harassment policies protecting students based on sexual orientation, gender identity, religion, race, color, national origin, sex, and disability.
EventItemMatterName: Tyler Clementi Higher Education Anti-Harassment Act (H.R. 2151/S.954)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign the Humane Alternatives to Long-Term Solitary Confinement Act.
EventItemMatterName: Humane Alternatives to Long-Term Solitary Confinement Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Criminal Justice
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on federal and New York state authorities to appoint special prosecutors to prosecute violence and civil rights violations against individuals in the New York City Department of Correction.
EventItemMatterName: Appoint special prosecutors to prosecute violence and civil rights violations against individuals in the NYC Dept of Correction.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City University of New York (CUNY) to incorporate Lunar New Year as an observed university holiday throughout the CUNY system.
EventItemMatterName: CUNY to incorporate Lunar New Year as an observed university holiday throughout the CUNY system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Higher Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the City University of New York (CUNY) to incorporate the Muslim holidays of Eid Ul-Fitr and Eid Ul-Adha as observed university holidays throughout the CUNY system.
EventItemMatterName: CUNY to incorporate the Muslim holidays of Eid Ul-Fitr and Eid Ul-Adha as observed university holidays throughout the CUNY system.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Department of Homeland Security to terminate the use of privately-run immigration detention facilities, as well as to limit the use of detention to only those individuals who pose an imminent threat to national security
EventItemMatterName: US Dept of Homeland Security to terminate the use of privately-run immigration detention facilities, as well as to limit the use of detention to only those individuals who pose an imminent threat to national security.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the State Legislature to enact and for the Governor to sign A.1018 and S.2888, which would amend the State Vehicle and Traffic law to include “electric assisted” bicycles in the definition of bicycles and thus permit their use
EventItemMatterName: Include “electric assisted” bicycles in the definition of bicycles and thus permit their use. (A.1018 and S.2888)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to mandate that the New York State Education Department include intimate partner abuse awareness and prevention programs in all public middle school and high school athletic programs.
EventItemMatterName: Mandate that the NYS Education Dept include intimate partner abuse awareness and prevention programs in all public middle school and high school athletic programs.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the Governor to sign into law A5667A/S4769A, in relation to gravity knives.
EventItemMatterName: Gravity Knives (A.5667-A/S. 4769-A)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and Governor to sign legislation requiring New York State Homes and Community Renewal to collect succession rights data from property owners and release a summary of the statistics to the public.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring NYS Homes and Community Renewal to collect succession rights data from property owners and release a summary of the statistics to the public.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.5324, which would require the New York City Department of Transportation to allow New York City homeowners to repair curbs adjacent to their sidewalk and receive a tax credit for the cost of the repair.
EventItemMatterName: Require the NYC DOT to allow NYC homeowners to repair curbs adjacent to their sidewalk and receive a tax credit for the cost of the repair. (A.5324)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: Resolution condemning the repeal of Federal Communications Commission regulations requiring Internet Service Providers to obtain consumer consent before using or sharing sensitive consumer information and calling on the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign A.7191-B/S.5603-B, which would require all Internet Service Providers offering services to New York State customers to keep all customer information confidential unless written consent is provided by the customer
EventItemMatterName: Require all Internet Service Providers offering services to NYS customers to keep all customer information confidential unless written consent is provided by the customer. (A.7191-B/S.5603-B)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation that would make killing someone while driving and using a phone or handheld device a felony and seriously injuring someone while driving and using a phone or handheld device a misdemeanor.
EventItemMatterName: Legislation that would make killing someone while driving and using a phone or handheld device a felony and seriously injuring someone while driving and using a phone or handheld device a misdemeanor.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the Metropolitan Transportation Authority to timely post and publicly announce information regarding all elevator service interruptions along with suggested alternatives.
EventItemMatterName: MTA to timely post and publicly announce information regarding all elevator service interruptions along with suggested alternatives.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Assembly to pass, the New York State Senate to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign legislation, providing for increases pursuant to changes in the consumer price index for the senior citizen rent increase exemption (SCRIE).
EventItemMatterName: Increases pursuant to changes in the consumer price index for the senior citizen rent increase exemption (SCRIE).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass legislation requiring all New York City charter schools to reserve 5% of their seats for late-enrolling “over the counter” students.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all NYC charter schools to reserve 5% of their seats for late-enrolling “over the counter” students.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Department of Education to offer kosher and halal meals in the Summer Meals Program.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to offer kosher and halal meals in the Summer Meals Program.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass and for the President to sign H.R. 1013, also known as the Regulate Marijuana Like Alcohol Act.
EventItemMatterName: Regulate Marijuana Like Alcohol Act. (H.R. 1013)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign legislation requiring all U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) agents to wear body cameras during field operations and removal proceedings, in order to increase ICE and CBP accountability, and ensure that immigration enforcement activities are conducted in a safe and lawful manner
EventItemMatterName: Requiring all U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) and U.S. Customs and Border Protection (CBP) agents to wear body cameras during field operations and removal proceedings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Department of Education to implement a robust requirement for civics education at the elementary, middle and high school level for all public schools in New York.
EventItemMatterName: DOE to implement a robust requirement for civics education at the elementary, middle and high school level for all public schools in NY.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass, and the Governor to sign, legislation removing the statute of limitations for rent overcharges.
EventItemMatterName: Removing the statute of limitations for rent overcharges.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to seal housing court records until the case has been decided and to permanently seal such records if the tenant prevails.
EventItemMatterName: Seal housing court records until the case has been decided and to permanently seal such records if the tenant prevails.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of the Governor of New York State in the commitment to and facilitation of the development of large-scale offshore wind projects by 2030.
EventItemMatterName: Support of the Governor of NYS in the commitment to and facilitation of the development of large-scale offshore wind projects by 2030.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the New York State Legislature to amend the Penal Law Section 130.05 to include individuals in police custody as being categorically incapable of consenting to sexual conduct with a police officer
EventItemMatterName: NYS Legislature to amend the Penal Law Section 130.05 to include individuals in police custody as being categorically incapable of consenting to sexual conduct with a police officer.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Federal Aviation Administration to amend the North Shore helicopter route to extend further west to cover Northeast Queens.
EventItemMatterName: Federal Aviation Administration to amend the North Shore helicopter route to extend further west to cover Northeast Queens.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Congress to propose an amendment to the Constitution of the United States Section 1 of the 13th Amendment, to prohibit slavery and involuntary servitude as a punishment for a crime.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibit slavery and involuntary servitude as a punishment for a crime.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Food and Drug Administration to require warning labels on sugar sweetened beverages.
EventItemMatterName: Require warning labels on sugar sweetened beverages.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission to designate 5224 Tilden Avenue (Tax Block 4737, Tax Lot 10), Borough of Brooklyn, the home of Jackie Robinson, as an historic landmark pursuant to Section 3020 of the New York City Charter.
EventItemMatterName: Landmarks, designate 5224 Tilden Avenue, Brooklyn, the home of Jackie Robinson, as an historic landmark.

EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass, and the President to sign, H.R. 4937, which would provide immigration relief for New York resident Ravidath “Ravi” Lawrence Ragbir and denouncing the unlawful targeting of immigrant rights activists for deportation by the U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE)
EventItemMatterName: Provide immigration relief for NY resident Ravidath “Ravi” Lawrence Ragbir.
